typedef struct DPU_RangeProcHWA_EDMAOutputConfig_t DPU_RangeProcHWA_EDMAOutputConfig

RangeProc output EDMA configuration.

The structure is used to hold the EDMA configuration needed for Range FFT

Fmt1: Generic EDMA ping/pong output mode

  • 1 ping/pong EDMA channel,
  • 1 ping/pong HWA signature channel

Fmt2: Specific EDMA ping/pong output mode used ONLY for 3 TX anntenna for radar cube layout format: DPIF_RADARCUBE_FORMAT_1, ADCbuf interleave mode DPIF_RXCHAN_NON_INTERLEAVE_MODE

  • 1 ping/pong dummy EDMA channel with 3 shadow channels
  • 3 ping/pong dataOut channel
  • 1 ping/pong HWA signature channel

enum DPU_RangeProcHWA_InputMode_e

RangeProc data input mode.

This enum defines if the rangeProc input data is from RF front end or it is in M0 but standalone from RF.

Enumerator
DPU_RangeProcHWA_InputMode_MAPPED 

Range input is integrated with DFE input ADC buffer is mapped to HWA memory DMA data from ADC buffer to HWA is NOT required.

DPU_RangeProcHWA_InputMode_ISOLATED 

Range input is integrated with DFE input ADC buffer is not mapped to HWA memory, DMA data from ADCBuf to HWA memory is needed in range processing.
